Utilising selection-sort algorithm, this program checks if 2 phrases are anagrams.

An anagram is a rearrangement of all the original letters in a phrase, disregarding any non-letter characters. (not CaSe SeNsItIvE).

Eg: Mother-in-law =&gt; Woman Hitler (They are anagrams).

Code: <a href="https://harishv7.files.wordpress.com/2014/12/anagrams.docx">anagrams</a>

